	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">65024U wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">Is there a TCC  equivalent for TCC to assemble C++?</div>
<br />No. Just no. See <a href="http://yosefk.com/c++fqa/" class="postlink">just how much of a beast that language is</a>. As Stroustrup put it, "Within C++, there is a much smaller and cleaner subset struggling to get out," but every project seems to have a different idea of which C++ features are useful and which are bloat.

		

		</td>
